# **<u>Visualization of Data </u>**

The visualizations below were designed to clearly communicate relationship within the dataset and gain more insights on variables of interest that will be used. This component is separated into two main parts. Part A presents the demographic variables from the Jamaican labour Force Survey for July 2019 and July 2022 that provides and overview of the common demographic patterns within the labour force survey in the two periods. Part B focuses on key variables that will be asses along with the main demographic variables-Sex, to explore the presence of gender disparities in the Jamaican labour force. 


